mber one best seller on Amazon.com in three categories: humorous erotica, LGBT erotica, and gay erotica.<ref name=\"micnumberone\" /><ref name=\"theweek\">{{citation|title=Erotic Donald Trump novella tops Amazon charts|date=January 26, 2016|url=http://www.theweek.co.uk/68933/erotic-donald-trump-novella-tops-amazon-charts|work=[[The Week]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170509115751/http://www.theweek.co.uk/68933/erotic-donald-trump-novella-tops-amazon-charts|url-status=live|access-date=July 18, 2017|archivedate=May 9, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"mediaite\">{{citation|last=Ellefson|first=Lindsey|title=Amazon Customers Make Erotica Great Again by Making Sexy Trump Novella Top E-Book|date=January 26, 2016|url=http://www.mediaite.com/online/amazon-customers-make-erotica-great-again-by-making-sexy-trump-novella-top-e-book/|work=[[Mediaite]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170731145337/http://www.mediaite.com/online/amazon-customers-make-erotica-great-again-by-making-sexy-trump-novella-top-e-book/|url-status=live|access-date=July 18, 2017|archivedate=July 31, 2017}}</ref> The book was listed on Amazon above ''Fifty Shades of Grey'' by [[E. L. James]],<ref name=\"hpde\" /> and was featured in ''[[The Washington Post]]'',<ref name=\"dyer\" /> ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'',<ref name=\"schaub\">{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/books/jacketcopy/la-et-jc-donald-trump-erotica-novel-huuuge-amazon-hit-20160126-story.html|title=Donald Trump erotica novel is a huuuge hit on Amazon|last1=Schaub|first1=Michael|date=January 26, 2017|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170603191154/http://www.latimes.com/books/jacketcopy/la-et-jc-donald-trump-erotica-novel-huuuge-amazon-hit-20160126-story.html|archivedate=June 3, 2017|url-status=live|access-date=July 18, 2017}}</ref> ''[[GQ]]'',<ref name=\"gqmagazine\" /> ''[[Gay Star News]]'',<ref name=\"gaystarnews\">{{citation|last=Morgan|first=Joe|title=The 7 most hilarious lines from the gay kinky sex novel about Donald Trump|date=January 27, 2016|url=https://www.gaystarnews.com/article/gay-novella-donald-trump/|work=[[Gay Star News]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160318005618/http://www.gaystarnews.com/article/gay-novella-donald-trump/|url-status=live|access-date=July 18, 2017|archivedate=March 18, 2016}}</ref> ''[[Evening Standard|London Evening Standard]]'',<ref name=\"standard\" /> ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'',<ref name=\"roberttait\" /> and ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]''.<ref name=\"mcmanus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/read/meet-the-comedian-who-wrote-a-hit-erotic-novella-starring-donald-trump|title=Meet the Comedian Who Wrote a Hit Erotic Novella Starring Donald Trump|last1=McManus|first1=Brian|date=January 22, 2016|work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160605185358/http://www.vice.com/read/meet-the-comedian-who-wrote-a-hit-erotic-novella-starring-donald-trump|archivedate=June 5, 2016|url-status=live|access-date=July 18, 2017}}</ref> ''[[The Guardian]]'' classed the work as part of the \"small but burgeoning new genre: satirical books about Donald Trump\" that began with the 2016 presidential campaign.<ref name=\"guardiansatire\">{{Citation|last=Flood|first=Alison|title=Picture books and porn: mini-boom in satirical titles inspired by Donald Trump|date=July 27, 2016|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/jul/27/picture-books-and-porn-mini-boom-in-satirical-titles-inspired-by-donald-trump|work=[[The Guardian]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170607210702/https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/jul/27/picture-books-and-porn-mini-boom-in-satirical-titles-inspired-by-donald-trump|url-status=live|access-date=July 18, 2017|archivedate=June 7, 2017}}</ref> ''[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]'' called the book a literary success.<ref name=\"cosmopolitan\">{{Citation|last=Smothers|first=Hannah|title=9 Steamy Excerpts From Donald Trump Erotica That Will Leave You Hot and Bothered|date=January 25, 2016|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.com/sex-love/news/a52655/steamy-donald-trump-erotica-excerpts/|work=[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118213320/http://www.cosmopolitan.com/sex-love/news/a52655/steamy-donald-trump-erotica-excerpts/|url-status=live|access-date=July 18, 2017|archivedate=January 18, 2017}}</ref> Daniel's book attracted 900,000 readers on the [[Wattpad]] website.<ref name=\"filmau\">{{Citation|last=Whigham|first=Nick|title=Erotic novella about Donald Trump to be made into a film|date=May 25, 2016|url=http://www.news.com.au/technology/online/social/erotic-novella-about-donald-trump-to-be-made-into-a-film-unless-he-can-stop-it/news-story/209116768b0184ffae4f6dcab6e21c14|work=[[News.com.au]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705141423/http://www.news.com.au/technology/online/social/erotic-novella-about-donald-trump-to-be-made-into-a-film-unless-he-can-stop-it/news-story/209116768b0184ffae4f6dcab6e21c14|url-status=live|access-date=July 18, 2017|archivedate=July 5, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"dailydotfilm\">{{citation|last=Sankin|first=Aaron|title=A best-selling erotic novel about Donald Trump is being made into full-blown porn|date=May 24, 2016|url=https://www.dailydot.com/layer8/donald-trump-porn-trump-temptations-movie/|work=[[The Daily Dot]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170705141421/https://www.dailydot.com/layer8/donald-trump-porn-trump-temptations-movie/|url-status=live|access-date=July 18, 2017|archivedate=July 5, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"soldani\">{{Citation|last=Soldani|first=Bianca|title=Brace yourselves, Donald Trump erotic fiction is being turned into a porno|date=May 25, 2016|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/news/thefeed/article/2016/05/25/brace-yourselves-donald-trump-erotic-fiction-being-turned-porno|work=SBS|access-date=July 18, 2017}}</ref> Daniel hired Trump impersonator Chris Ferretti to read the audiobook.<ref name=\"dyer\" /><ref>{{citation|last=Richter|first=Greg|title=Trump Featured in Erotic E-book with Huge Amazon Sales|date=January 26, 2016|url=http://www.newsmax.com/Politics/donald-trump-erotica-amazon-gay/2016/01/26/id/711114/|work=[[Newsmax]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304010422/http://www.newsmax.com/Politics/donald-trump-erotica-amazon-gay/2016/01/26/id/711114/|url-status=live|access-date=July 18, 2017|archivedate=March 4, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"gaw\">{{citation|last=Gaw|first=Kathryn|title=Trump Temptations: The Billionaire & The Bellboy - Donald Trump wins new fans as erotica novel climbs Amazon's bestseller charts|date=January 29, 2016|url=http://www.cityam.com/233403/trump-temptations-the-billionaire-the-bellboy-donald-trump-wins-new-fans-as-erotica-novel-climbs-amazons-bestseller-charts|work=[[City A.M.]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170316173514/http://www.cityam.com/233403/trump-temptations-the-billionaire-the-bellboy-donald-trump-wins-new-fans-as-erotica-novel-climbs-amazons-bestseller-charts|url-status=live|access-date=July 18, 2017|archivedate=March 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2016, Daniel negotiated a rights deal with film studio NakedSword to turn his novel into a [[feature film]].<ref name=\"filmau\" /><ref name=\"dailydotfilm\" /><ref name=\"soldani\" /> They began adapting the story in 2016.<ref name=\"filmau\" /><ref name=\"soldani\" /><ref name=\"attitude\">{{citation|last=Headspeath|first=Andrew|title=A Donald Trump gay porn parody in the works|date=May 25, 2016|url=http://attitude.co.uk/a-donald-trump-gay-porn-parody-in-the-works/|work=[[Attitude (magazine)|Attitude]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160901095430/http://attitude.co.uk/a-donald-trump-gay-porn-parody-in-the-works/|url-status=live|access-date=July 18, 2017|archivedate=September 1, 2016}}</ref> NakedSword stated they were interested in the project due to the absurd nature of the plot.<ref name=\"filmau\" /><ref name=\"dailydotfilm\" /><ref name=\"soldani\" /> Trump biographer Marc Shapiro wrote in ''Trump This!'' that Daniel's novel was one of the most infamous works capitalizing on interest in Trump.<ref name=\"marcshapiro\" /> An article in ''[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]]'' said that Daniel displayed a Trump-like skill to capitalize on a niche demand.<ref name=\"fortune\">{{Citation|last=Bukszpan|first=Daniel|title=Make Your Coffee Table Great Again. Here's All of the Books Coming Out About Trump|date=May 26, 2016|url=http://fortune.com/2016/05/26/books-about-donald-trump/|work=[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803213306/http://fortune.com/2016/05/26/books-about-donald-trump/|url-status=live|access-date=July 18, 2017|archivedate=August 3, 2017}}</ref>\n\n;Hell, Michigan\nOn August 30, 2017, Elijah Daniel performed a publicity stunt centered around [[Hell, Michigan]] \u2013 an unincorporated town that allows visitors to pay for the opportunity to hold the title of \"mayor\" for a day.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/hell-michigan-elijah-daniel-heterosexuality_us_59a735fde4b07e81d354ffa6|title=Mayor Of Hell, Inspired By Trump, Declares Heterosexuality Illegal|last=Moye|first=David|date=2017-08-30|work=Huffington Post|access-date=2017-08-31|language=en-US}}</ref> In what he called \"a copy-and-paste of Trump's [[Executive Order 13769|Muslim ban]]\", he announced a satirical law that banned heterosexuals from entering and living in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://live105.cbslocal.com/2017/08/30/comedian-becomes-mayor-of-hell-michigan-bans-heterosexuals-from-entering-town/|title=Comedian Becomes 'Mayor' Of Hell, Michigan; Bans Heterosexuals From Entering Town|access-date=2017-08-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170831022623/http://live105.cbslocal.com/2017/08/30/comedian-becomes-mayor-of-hell-michigan-bans-heterosexuals-from-entering-town/|archive-date=2017-08-31|url-status=dead}}</ref> In response, Daniel released an edited version of [[The Bible]] called ''The Holy Bible... but Gayer'' two weeks later. Sales of it were briefly banned on [[Amazon.com|Amazon]] before being restored.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/elijah-daniel-gay-bible_us_59c01193e4b06f9bf048872f|title=Former Mayor Of Hell Rewrites Bible To Make It Really, Really Gay|first=David|last=Moye|publisher=The Huffington Post|date=2017-09-18|accessdate=2017-09-19}}</ref> {{anchor|Gay Hell}}On June 17, 2019, Elijah Daniel claimed that he briefly \"bought\" the incorporated hamlet of [[Hell, Michigan]], changed its name to Gay Hell, Michigan and created a law prohibiting any flag other than pride flags from flying in the town. This was done in retaliation to the Trump administration's ban on the flying of the gay pride flag by U.S. embassies.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Daniel |first1=Elijah |url=https://twitter.com/elijahdaniel/status/1140711709939814400}}</ref>\n\n;Television\nIn November 2017, Daniel, Christine Sydelko and [[Tana Mongeau]] appeared on a segment of [[Maury (talk show)|''The Maury Povich Show'']] in which they pretended to be engaged after Daniel having proposed to Christine at [[Taco Bell]]. Christine feared Daniel was cheating on her with Mongeau, but Daniel's lie detector results revealed he was actually cheating with men.<ref>{{Citation|title=Is Elijah Cheating on Christine with Tana? {{!}} The Maury Show|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4VC1Kw18dlA|language=en|access-date=2019-08-25}}</ref>\n\n===2019\u2013present: Music===\nSince 2017, Daniel has been releasing hip hop music under the stage name Lil Phag. He has released two extended plays and one studio album under the moniker, as well as slew of singles with artists including CupcaKke, Bella Thorne, Tana Mongeau, and Dr. Woke, the latter of whom producer most of his music. The pair have since gone on to form their own musical project, Adam&Steve, which has a more EDM sound.\n\n==Personal life==\nAs of 2017, Daniel resides in Los Angeles, California.<ref name=binderpaper /><ref name=\"orfanides\"/> In January 2019, Daniel announced his engagement to boyfriend Sam, professionally known as Dr. Woke.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/elijahdaniel/status/1083946245813608448|title=im really fuckin engaged to someone who has Tana's name in bold font tattooed on his fucking leg u know what maybe the engagement is off alreadyhttps://twitter.com/DJSamF/status/1083945839565918210\u00a0\u2026|first=elijah|last=daniel|date=January 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wetheunicorns.com/youtubers/elijah-daniel/engaged-dr-woke/|title=Elijah Daniel just got engaged and the pictures are too cute|website=We The Unicorns}}</ref>\n\n===LGBT advocacy===\nAfter the [[2016 Orlando nightclub shooting|Orlando nightclub shooting]] in June 2016, Daniel publicly urged on Twitter for any [[closeted]] people to feel free to contact him privately for support,<ref name=tongco>{{citation|url=https://www.attn.com/stories/9156/elijah-daniel-using-twitter-to-help-lgbt-community-come-out|work=[[ATTN:]]|access-date=July 18, 2017|title=Elijah Daniel's Powerful Response to the Orlando Attack|last=Tongco|first=Tricia|date=June 14, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804013707/https://www.attn.com/stories/9156/elijah-daniel-using-twitter-to-help-lgbt-community-come-out|archivedate=August 4, 2017}}</ref> and he published \"An open letter to the LGBT kids who feel lost and scared\" on [[Fusion.net]].<ref name=tongco /><ref name=openletter>{{Citation|title=An open letter to the LGBT kids who feel lost and scared|access-date=July 18, 2017|first=Elijah|last=Daniel|date=June 13, 2016|url=http://fusion.kinja.com/an-open-letter-to-the-lgbt-kids-who-feel-lost-and-scare-1793857510|work=[[Fusion.net]]}}</ref> The letter positively was received by [[ATTN:]], which called it a powerful commentary on the attack.<ref name=tongco />\n\nAfter receiving homophobic [[death threat|death threats]] via Twitter, in July 2016 Daniel messaged someone he believed to be the parents of the user about the incident and publicly posted a screenshot of his message to them.<ref name=calmresponse>{{citation|url=http://metro.co.uk/2016/07/20/man-handles-receiving-homophobic-death-threats-incredibly-calmly-6018673/|access-date=July 18, 2017|work=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro News]]|title=Man handles receiving homophobic death threats incredibly calmly|first=Hattie|last=Gladwell|date=July 20, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804052959/http://metro.co.uk/2016/07/20/man-handles-receiving-homophobic-death-threats-incredibly-calmly-6018673/|archivedate=August 4, 2017}}</ref><ref name=elitebest>{{Citation|url=http://elitedaily.com/social-news/guy-best-response-man-sending-homophobic-death-threats/1559148/|work=[[Elite Daily]]|access-date=July 18, 2017|title=Guy Had Best Response To Man Sending Him Homophobic Death Threats|first=Alec|last=MacDonald|date=July 20, 2016}}</ref> His response was praised by ''[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro News]]'' and ''[[Elite Daily]]''.<ref name=calmresponse /><ref name=elitebest />\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\nElijah Daniel and Christine Sydelko jointly won Best Comedian from the [[9th Shorty Awards|Shorty Awards]] in 2017.<ref name=shortyawards /><ref name=wininterview>{{citation|access-date=July 18, 2017|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nt2fFgsHesk|date=April 26, 2017|title=Christine Sydelko and Elijah Daniel Shorty Awards Winner Interview|work=[[Shorty Awards]]|publisher=YouTube|type=video}}</ref> Daniel received a positive reception for his comedy posted via [[video blogging]] and [[social media]], from [[Heavy.com]],<ref name=orfanides>{{citation|first=Effie|last=Orfanides|work=[[Heavy.com]]|access-date=July 17, 2017|date=July 5, 2017|url=http://heavy.com/entertainment/2017/07/elijah-daniel-dead-death-hoax-twitter-who-is/|title=Elijah Daniel Death Hoax Confuses Fans|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706043742/http://heavy.com/entertainment/2017/07/elijah-daniel-dead-death-hoax-twitter-who-is/|archivedate=July 6, 2017}}</ref> ''[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]'',<ref name=binderpaper /> ''[[The Washington Post]]'',<ref name=dyer /> and ''[[The Daily Dot]]''.<ref name=\"ohara\"/>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Studio albums===\n* ''God Hates Lil Phag'' (2018)\n\n===Extended plays===\n* ''ResERECTION'' (2019)\n* ''Antichrist'' (2019)\n* ''The Final Album'' (2019) No. 138 US<ref>{{cite tweet|user=billboardcharts|number=1214205411097792513|title=Debuts on this week's #Billboard200|date=January 6, 2020|accessdate=January 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Singles===\n'''As lead artist'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/artist/29XJC5N8MrBCo3XgUU1KPk|title=LIL PHAG|website=Spotify|language=en|access-date=2018-01-07}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"1\"| Year\n! rowspan=\"1\"| Album\n|-\n|\"Phaggot\"\n| rowspan=\"5\" |2017\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''God Hates Lil Phag''\n|-\n|\"Elton John\"<br/><small>(with [[Hoodie Allen]] and Dr. Woke)</small>\n|-\n|\"Gucci Christmas\"<br/><small>(with Dr. Woke)</small>\n| {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n|\"Deadahh\"<br/><small>(with [[Tana Mongeau]] and Dr. Woke)</small>\n|''God Hates Lil Phag''\n|-\n|\"Phucked Ur Dad\"\n| {{n/a|Non-album single}}\n|-\n|\"Clout 9\"<br/><small>(with [[Bella Thorne]], Tana Mongeau and Dr. Woke)</small>\n| rowspan=\"7\" |2018\n| rowspan=\"5\" |''God Hates Lil Phag''\n|-\n|\":)\"<br/><small>(with [[Mod Sun|MOD SUN]] and Dr. Woke)</small>\n|-\n|\"Rick and Morty\"<br/><small>(with Rico Nasty and Dr. Woke)</small>\n|-\n|\"3AM Anxiety\"<br/><small>(with Dr. Woke)</small>\n|-\n|\"Iced Out Dick\"<br/><small>(with [[Cupcakke]] and Dr. Woke)</small>\n|-\n|\"Third Eye Gucci\"<br/><small>(with Dr. Woke)</small>\n|{{TBA}}\n|-\n|\"It's My Money, And I Need It Now\"<br/><small>(with Dr. Woke)</small>\n|''God Hates Lil Phag''\n|-\n|\"ERRYBODYGAY\"<br/><small>(with Dr. 