 2014}}\n</ref>\n\n}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{Citation|access-date=July 18, 2017|url=http://shortyawards.com/9th/elijahdaniel|title=From the 9th Annual Shorty Awards - Elijah Daniel & Christine Sydelko - Winner in Comedy|work=[[9th Shorty Awards|9th Annual Shorty Awards]]|agency=[[Shorty Awards]]|date=April 23, 2017|archivedate=June 6, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170606074000/http://shortyawards.com/9th/elijahdaniel|ref=none}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Twitter | id= elijahdaniel | name= Elijah Daniel }}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Daniel, Elijah}}\n[[Category:1994 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:American erotica writers]]\n[[Category:American male comedians]]\n[[Category:American satirists]]\n[[Category:American male non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Comedians from California]]\n[[Category:Gay actors]]\n[[Category:Gay artists]]\n[[Category:Gay writers]]\n[[Category:LGBT rappers]]\n[[Category:Gay rappers]]\n[[Category:LGBT musicians from the United States]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Michigan]]\n[[Category:LGBT comedians]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Detroit]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Video bloggers]]\n[[Category:Male bloggers]]\n", "name_user": "Dizzydizzydeja", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(added a citation)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elijah_Daniel"}
{"title_page": "Pension Sch\u00f6ller (1960 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|1960 film}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Pension Sch\u00f6ller \n| image =Pension Sch\u00f6ller (1960 film).jpg\n| caption =\n| director = [[Georg Jacoby]] \n| producer =  {{ubl|[[Walter Koppel]]|[[Gyula Trebitsch]]}}\n| writer =  {{ubl|[[Carl Laufs]] (play)|[[Wilhelm Jacoby]] (play)|Georg Jacoby|[[Joachim Wedekind]]}}\n| narrator =\n| starring = {{ubl|[[Theo Lingen]]|[[Christa Williams]]|[[Ann Smyrner]]}}\n| music = [[Martin B\u00f6ttcher]]  \n| cinematography = [[Willy Winterstein]]  \n| editing =     [[Alice Ludwig]]\n| studio = [[Real Film]] \n| distributor =Europa-Filmverleih\n| released =  15 July 1960 \n| runtime = 93 minutes\n| country = West Germany\n| language = [[German language|German]] \n| budget =\n| gross =\n}}\n'''''Pension Sch\u00f6ller''''' is a 1960 [[Cinema of Germany|West German]] [[comedy film]] directed by [[Georg Jacoby]] and starring [[Theo Lingen]], [[Christa Williams]] and [[Rudolf Vogel]].<ref>Bock & Bergfelder p.223</ref> It is an adaptation of the 1890 play ''[[Pension Sch\u00f6ller (play)|Pension Sch\u00f6ller]]'' by [[Wilhelm Jacoby]] and [[Carl Laufs]]. Georg Jacoby was Wilhem's son, and made three film adaptation of his father's best known play in 1930, 1952 and 1960.\n\nIt was shot at the [[Wandsbek Studios]] in [[Hamburg]]. The film's sets were designed by the [[art director]]s [[Albrecht Becker]] and [[Herbert Kirchhoff]].\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Theo Lingen]] as Professor Sch\u00f6ller\n* [[Christa Williams]] as Fritzi\n* [[Rudolf Vogel]] as Gutsbesitzer Klapproth\n* [[Boy Gobert]] as Eugen R\u00fcmpel\n* [[Ann Smyrner]] as Erika\n* [[Helmut Lohner]] as Peter Klapproth\n* [[Ilse Steppat]] as Amalie Sch\u00f6ller\n* [[Leon Askin]] as Fritz Bernhardi\n* [[Ursula Herking]] as Josefine Kr\u00fcger\n* [[Rainer Bertram]] as Tommy Kiesling\n* [[Christa Siems]] as Ulrike Klapproth\n* [[Benno Gellenbeck]] as Artist Zarini\n* [[Joachim Wolff]]\n* [[Henry Vahl]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* Bergfelder, Tim & Bock, Hans-Michael. ''The Concise Cinegraph: Encyclopedia of German. Berghahn Books, 2009.\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|0054171|Pension Sch\u00f6ller}}\n\n{{Georg Jacoby}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pension Scholler (1960 film)}}\n[[Category:1960 films]]\n[[Category:1960 comedy films]]\n[[Category:German comedy films]]\n[[Category:West German films]]\n[[Category:German-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Georg Jacoby]]\n[[Category:German films based on plays]]\n[[Category:German film remakes]]\n[[Category:Real Film films]]\n[[Category:Films shot at Wandsbek Studios]]\n{{1960s-Germany-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1960 film}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Pension Sch\u00f6ller \n| image =Pension Sch\u00f6ller (1960 film).jpg\n| caption =\n| director = [[Georg Jacoby]] \n| producer =  {{ubl|[[Walter Koppel]]|[[Gyula Trebitsch]]}}\n| writer =  {{ubl|[[Carl Laufs]] (play)|[[Wilhelm Jacoby]] (play)|Georg Jacoby|[[Joachim Wedekind]]}}\n| narrator =\n| starring = {{ubl|[[Theo Lingen]]|[[Christa Williams]]|[[Ann Smyrner]]}}\n| music = [[Martin B\u00f6ttcher]]  \n| cinematography = [[Willy Winterstein]]  \n| editing =     [[Alice Ludwig]]\n| studio = [[Real Film]] \n| distributor =Europa-Filmverleih\n| released =  15 July 1960 \n| runtime = 93 minutes\n| country = West Germany\n| language = [[German language|German]] \n| budget =\n| gross =\n}}\n'''''Pension Sch\u00f6ller''''' is a 1960 [[Cinema of Germany|West German]] [[comedy film]] directed by [[Georg Jacoby]] and starring [[Theo Lingen]], [[Christa Williams]] and [[Rudolf Vogel]].<ref>Bock & Bergfelder p.223</ref> It is an adaptation of the 1890 play ''[[Pension Sch\u00f6ller (play)|Pension Sch\u00f6ller]]'' by [[Wilhelm Jacoby]] and [[Carl Laufs]]. Georg Jacoby was Wilhem's son, and made three film adaptation of his father's best known play in 1930, 1952 and 1960.\n\nIt was shot at the [[Wandsbek Studios]] in [[Hamburg]]. The film's sets were designed by the [[art director]]s [[Albrecht Becker]] and [[Herbert Kirchhoff]].\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Theo Lingen]] as Professor Sch\u00f6ller\n* [[Christa Williams]] as Fritzi\n* [[Rudolf Vogel]] as Gutsbesitzer Klapproth\n* [[Boy Gobert]] as Eugen R\u00fcmpel\n* [[Ann Smyrner]] as Erika\n* [[Helmut Lohner]] as Peter Klapproth\n* [[Ilse Steppat]] as Amalie Sch\u00f6ller\n* [[Leon Askin]] as Fritz Bernhardi\n* [[Ursula Herking]] as Josefine Kr\u00fcger\n* [[Rainer Bertram]] as Tommy Kiesling\n* [[Christa Siems]] as Ulrike Klapproth\n* [[Benno Gellenbeck]] as Artist Zarini\n* [[Joachim Wolff]]\n* [[Henry Vahl]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* Bergfelder, Tim & Bock, Hans-Michael. ''The Concise Cinegraph: Encyclopedia of German. Berghahn Books, 2009.\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|0054171|Pension Sch\u00f6ller}}\n\n{{Georg Jacoby}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pension Scholler (1960 film)}}\n[[Category:1960 films]]\n[[Category:1960s comedy films]]\n[[Category:German comedy films]]\n[[Category:West German films]]\n[[Category:German-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Georg Jacoby]]\n[[Category:German films based on plays]]\n[[Category:German film remakes]]\n[[Category:Real Film films]]\n[[Category:Films shot at Wandsbek Studios]]\n{{1960s-Germany-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "BrownHairedGirl", "label": "safe", "comment": "Moving fromCategory:1960s comedy filmstoCategory:1960 comedy filmsusingCat-a-lot", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pension_Sch%C3%B6ller_(1960_film)"}
