. Smith\n* Gonzalo Amat\n}}\n| editor                   = {{Plainlist|\n* Sunny Hodge\n* Christal Khatib\n* [[Jeffrey M. Werner]]\n* Kyle Bond\n* Scott Wallace\n* Blake Maniquis\n* John Peter Bernardo\n}}\n| camera                   = \n| runtime                  = 46\u201356 minutes\n| company                  = {{Plainlist|\n* Rock Fish\n* Red Canoe Productions\n}}\n| network                  = [[Netflix]]\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2020|4|15}}\n| last_aired               = <!--{{End date|present}}-->\n| website                  = https://www.netflix.com/title/80236318\n| website_title            = Official website\n}}\n\n'''''Outer Banks''''' is an American [[Action film|action]]\u2013[[Adventure film|adventure]] [[Mystery fiction|mystery]] [[teen drama]] [[web television]] series created by [[Josh Pate]], [[Jonas Pate]], and [[Shannon Burke (writer)|Shannon Burke]] that premiered on April 15, 2020.<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\"/><ref name=\"ReleaseDate\"/> This Tv series is viewable on Netflix. \n\n==Premise==\n''Outer Banks'' follows a group of teenagers in the [[Outer Banks of North Carolina]] who are called \"Pogues\" and are determined to find out what happened to the \" ringleader's missing father\". Along the way, they discover a legendary treasure that is tied to his father.<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\"/> All of this seemed possible until they ran into some trouble. Chased by the law and the \"Kooks\", also known as the wealthy and superior group, these teens found themselves running more then they could have ever imagined. The treasure was obtainable but they have to go through many obstacles to get there. Drugs, love, fighting, friendship, money and how the rich keep on winning. A group of Pogues will do whatever it takes in order to finish and honor John B's missing fathers goal that he had been working on for 20 years.  \n\n<br />\n\n==Cast and characters==\n<gallery>\n</gallery>\n\n===Main Cast Members ===\n<!--Main cast order is according to original credits (the pilot episode). Do NOT rearrange cast order, per MOS:TVCAST. In addition, new main cast members will be at the bottom of the list.-->\n* Chase Stokes as John B, the ringleader of the Pogues\n* Madelyn Cline as Sarah Cameron, the princess of the Kooks\n* Madison Bailey as Kiara \"Kie\", a trust fund kid who hangs out with the Pogues and Sarah's former best friend\n* Jonathan Daviss as Pope, the brains of the Pogues\n* Rudy Pankow as JJ, John B's best friend since the third grade who is a surfer\n* [[Austin North]] as Topper, Sarah's boyfriend and fellow Kook who despises the Pogues\n* [[Charles Esten]] as Ward Cameron, John B's boss and Sarah's father\n* Drew Starkey as Rafe Cameron, Sarah's older brother\n\n===Recurring Cast Members ===\n<!--Reliably sourced and/or confirmed to make 4+ appearances in the series. -->\n* [[Adina Porter]] as Sheriff Peterkin, the local sheriff\n* [[Cullen Moss]] as Deputy Shoupe\n* Julia Antonelli as Wheezie Cameron, Sarah and Rafe's younger sister\n* Caroline Arapoglou as Rose, the Cameron siblings' stepmother and Ward's wife\n* [[E. Roger Mitchell]] as Heyward, Pope's father\n* CC Castillo as Lana Grubbs, the widow of a man named Scooter Grubbs who was killed during Hurricane Agatha\n* Chelle Ramos as Deputy Plumb\n* Brian Stapf as Cruz\n* Marland Burke as Mike\n* Deion Smith as Kelce, Rafe's friend\n* Nicholas Cirillo as Barry, Rafe's drug dealer and the owner of a pawn shop\n* [[Gary Weeks]] as Luke, JJ's father\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |background=#302A27 |overall= |title= |director= |writer=|airdate=|released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Pilot\n |DirectedBy      = [[Jonas Pate]]\n |WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Josh Pate & Jonas Pate & Shannon Burke|t=[[Josh Pate]] & [[Shannon Burke (writer)|Shannon Burke]]|tfirst=y}}\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|15}}\n |ShortSummary    = <!-- Episode summaries must be expressed in your own words. Do NOT s